ecromancer class.  I really wanna play on SZ on the good team, just because of the challenge of being a good, but I wanna play a necromancer kinda, so I have decided to go to Rallos and try my luck.  <br>
<br>
I was hoping someone could tell me abit about there play style in pvp?  I guess I should go to a necro board to ask this, but this forum is more helpfull from what I can tell.  I was wondering how necromancers did at the later lvls, with AA abilities and such.  <br>
<br>
I was thinking about going Iksar, just becuase I have never played an Iksar before and I heard that Iksar necromancers are pretty nice.  I understand that talent has a lot to do with pvp, but talent can only help so much when the class itself isn't any good at pvp.  <br>
<br>
My post is a little vague and if anyone needs more information please let me know, and I appreciate any information given.  <br>
<br>
Madox <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athousandyoung>AThousandYoung</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 5:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Necromancers</span><hr size=1> Go to a Necromancer board.<br>
<br>
Necros are the most powerful or one of the most powerful PvP classes there are, along with Wizards and Shadow Knights.  One could make a case for Bards too and a few other classes, but Necros are definitely near the top of the heap.<br>
<br>
Their strong points include a powerful pet, very low resist taps that are very powerful when you consider both the healing and damage, very nasty low resist DOTs, Shadow Step, Harmshield, Feign Death (for training and getting NPCs and sometimes pets off of them, if the owners aren't near), an instakill AA that does not suffer from the 75% max damage limit (lifeburn)...<br>
<br>
Probably the biggest advantage they have are very fast casting low resist taps...kind of a combination of a Lure and a Draught with a heal thrown in.<br>
